{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-create-coupon-codes-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Create Coupon Codes in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>Coupon codes are a proven marketing strategy for boosting sales and attracting customers to your online store. Magento 2 provides an intuitive platform for creating and managing coupon codes, offering a variety of options for setting conditions and discounts. In this blog, we will guide you through the process of creating a coupon code, from logging in to your <a href=\"https://experienceleague.adobe.com/docs/commerce-admin/start/admin/admin.html\">Magento 2 admin</a> panel to testing the coupon code at checkout.&nbsp;<br><br>With this comprehensive guide, you will be able to know <strong><em>how to create coupon codes in Magento 2</em></strong> store with ease. And then after you will also be able to <a href=\"/how-to-auto-apply-coupon-code-in-magento-2/\">auto apply coupon code in your Magento store</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to create Coupon Codes in Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Log in to your Magento 2 Admin Panel</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To access the coupon code feature, log in to your Magento 2 admin panel using your username and password.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://webguru.dev/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/how-to-create-coupon-codes-in-magento-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"-375\" height=\"-408\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Navigate to Marketing &gt; Promotions &gt; Cart Price Rules</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the left-side menu, click on Marketing and then Promotions. Under the Promotions tab, click on Cart Price Rules. This is where you will create and manage your coupon codes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://webguru.dev/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/how-to-create-coupon-codes-in-magento-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"-729\" height=\"-1008\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Create a New Cart Price Rule</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the &#8220;Add New Rule&#8221; button at the top right corner of the page. This will open the &#8220;New Cart Price Rule&#8221; page.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://webguru.dev/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/how-to-create-coupon-codes-in-magento-2-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"-65\" height=\"-26\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Fill in the Required Information</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter a descriptive name for your coupon code in the &#8220;Rule Name&#8221; field. In the &#8220;Customer Group&#8221; section, select the customer groups for which the coupon code will be valid. Then, set the &#8220;From&#8221; and &#8220;To&#8221; dates for when the coupon code will be active.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://webguru.dev/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/how-to-create-coupon-codes-in-magento-2-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"-43\" height=\"-17\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 5: Set the Coupon Code Conditions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the &#8220;Conditions&#8221; section, select the conditions under which the coupon code will be valid. For example, you can set a minimum purchase amount, a specific product, or a category for the coupon code to be valid.</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:480px;displa